Installation:
=============
1.  get latest from GitHub
      -- git clone https://github.com/jtsinoni/dmles-mobile-ionic.git
2.  cd to dmles-mobile-ionic
3.  npm install
4.  ionic prepare --nofetch (this adds the platforms and plugins to each platform)
5.  done

A few ionic commands
=====================
    -- ionic serve                          ## runs node.js and serves files, great during development, can make changes to code and autodeploys
    -- ionic emulate [android|ios]          ## builds and deploys to emulator

    ## Development Mode
    -- ionic run [android|ios]              ## builds and deploys to device
    -- ionic build [android|ios]            ## builds only

    ## Production Mode
    -- ionic run [android|ios] --prod       ## builds and deploys to device in prod mode
    -- ionic build [android|ios] --prod     ## builds only in prod mode
    
